<h2>What it is</h2>

<p>
  Tesselage is a situational awareness platform that fuses multiple information streams &mdash; communications, sensor data, reports, social media, IoT feeds &mdash; into a unified operational picture. Inspired by military Command, Control, Communications, Computers, Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (C⁴ISR) systems, adapted for civilian organizations that need real-time awareness across complex, distributed operations.
</p>

<hr />

<h2>Core capabilities</h2>

<div class="feature-block">
  <div class="feature-label">Integration</div>
  <h4>Multi-source data fusion</h4>
  <p>
    Ingests and correlates data from disparate sources: email, Slack/Teams, radio transcripts, GPS feeds, weather APIs, IoT sensors, incident reports, and social media. Normalizes everything into a common event model with spatial and temporal context.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="feature-block">
  <div class="feature-label">Intelligence</div>
  <h4>AI-powered analysis</h4>
  <p>
    Automated event detection, anomaly identification, and trend analysis across fused data streams. Natural language summarization of developing situations. Pattern recognition that surfaces correlations human operators would miss across hundreds of concurrent data feeds.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="feature-block">
  <div class="feature-label">Operations</div>
  <h4>Common operating picture</h4>
  <p>
    A shared, real-time visualization layer that gives every stakeholder &mdash; from field teams to executive leadership &mdash; appropriate views of the current operational state. Map-based, timeline-based, and graph-based views depending on the context.
  </p>
</div>

<hr />

<h2>Designed for</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Emergency management:</strong> Disaster response coordination across multiple agencies, NGOs, and volunteer organizations</li>
  <li><strong>Enterprise operations:</strong> Large-scale infrastructure monitoring, supply chain visibility, and incident response</li>
  <li><strong>Security operations:</strong> Physical and cyber security operations centers requiring multi-feed awareness</li>
  <li><strong>Event management:</strong> Large venue and multi-site event coordination with real-time safety monitoring</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h2>Architecture principles</h2>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Resilience first:</strong> Designed to operate in degraded conditions &mdash; partial connectivity, failed sensors, overloaded networks. The system degrades gracefully rather than failing completely.</li>
  <li><strong>Human-in-the-loop:</strong> AI augments human decision-making but never replaces it for critical actions. Every automated recommendation includes confidence levels and supporting evidence.</li>
  <li><strong>Data sovereignty:</strong> On-premise deployment option with full data residency controls. No data leaves your infrastructure unless explicitly configured.</li>
  <li><strong>Interoperability:</strong> Built on open standards (CAP, EDXL, GeoJSON) to integrate with existing emergency management and enterprise systems.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h2>Current status</h2>

<p>
  Tesselage is in active development. The data fusion engine and core analysis pipelines are functional. The visualization layer and multi-tenant deployment infrastructure are under construction.
</p>

